wikipedia_page.main: Lieutenant-Colonel George Rowland Stanley Baring, 3rd Earl of Cromer,  (28 July 1918 – 16 March 1991), styled Viscount Errington before 1953, was a British banker and diplomat. After serving during the Second World War, he was Governor of the Bank of England (1961–1966) and British Ambassador to the United States (1971–1974).
